4. Another reason may be this,<lb/>
because<lb/>
the consideration of our former misery,<lb/>
will greatly abate pride in the<lb/>
hearts of converted men; this will be a<lb/>
great means to abate and keep under<lb/>
pride, and advance humility in the hearts<lb/>
of Gods people: Beloved, a good man<lb/>
naturally is apt to be proud, we are not<lb/>
